ncy checks for specific models of cosmic birefringence.\nMoreover, we estimate that among all the possible birefringent bispectra,\n$\\langle\\delta\\alpha\\, TB\\rangle$ and $\\langle\\delta\\alpha\\,EB\\rangle$ are the\nones which contain the largest signal-to-noise ratio. Once the cosmic\nbirefringence signal is taken to be at the level of current constraints, we\nshow that these bispectra are within reach of future CMB experiments, as\nLiteBIRD.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 9 Feb 2022 17:28:45 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 17 Feb 2022 12:40:02 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 23 Mar 2022 08:38:00 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 17 May 2022 11:54:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-18"}
