cy regimes including 1)\nhigh spatial frequency detector pixel-to-pixel quantum efficiency variations,\n2) medium spatial frequency \"measles\" caused by particle deposition on the\ndetector or other focal-plane optics post-launch, and 3) low spatial frequency\ndetector fringing caused by self-interference due to internal reflections in\nthe detector substrate as well as low spatial frequency vignetting at the edges\nof the Coronagraph's field of view. We show that Uranus and Neptune can be used\nas astrophysical flat sources with high precision ($\\sim$0.5% relative error)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Feb 2022 03:36:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-11"}
